cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the problem of adversarial learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and computer security. The use of game theory and multiple classifiers suggests that this paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of deep neural network-based classifiers and text data suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the use of self-play and strategic selection of classifiers suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
